scenes.label: *from_AC_03_21
texts: I Loaded to the start of the Hihack and went through the same steps as before, but this time I got Oz to ask for the captain's BMI password.
All that was left was to put our ridiculous plan into action.

texts: Looking for ways to open a new channel, I checked the articles I'd been looking at this morning for anything useful.
302 was equipped with an antenna to receive signals from the surface via geosynchronous sats.
That meant that signals sent directly from the surface wouldn't reach it.
Hacking into a place with antennas that could send signals into geosynchronous orbit was way too difficult, though.
While scrolling through the articles, I noticed a diagram that made me realize something obvious.
Sats weren't the only things that could fly over planes.
If it's a date, then I'm your lady!
I wanna borrow one of the missiles you fired at the army.
You mean my Beary-Airy? But that was a drone.
Huh? I don't remember it having propellers.

options.chara: 汎用_ウィンド情報アプリ

texts: Anything unmanned and remote-controlled is a drone, Polly!

options.chara: 汎用_ウィンド情報アプリ

texts: So that's what a drone was...

options.chara: 汎用_ウィンド情報アプリ

texts: Anyways, I need one so I can open a channel to reach a plane mid-flight.

options.chara: 汎用_ウィンド情報アプリ
汎用_ウィンド情報アプリ

texts: Yeah. And then I'm gonna use that channel to hack the plane from the surface.

options.chara: 汎用_ウィンド情報アプリ

texts: A lot of people are in danger. I'm gonna need a virtuoso's help.

options.chara: 汎用_ウィンド情報アプリ

texts: I guess I can modify it to make it work...

scenes.label: *flag_on
texts: That was when something important finally dawned on me.
My graper hasn't been repaired yet...
I'd used Saving and Loading to make bank, but then Dub had dropped the repairs to go off and sulk in bed.
The only grapers in front of the building were the ones belonging to Cross and Wind.
Didn't you say you'd rather die than ride someone else's graper?
Mine's broken, bro. I got no choice here.
Plus, I used to make a living as an amateur racer. There's no graper I can't handle!
I'm not sure I follow your logic...
...but there, I gave you the rights to use it.
Not that you'll listen, but...don't be reckless, alright?
I used my BMI to turn on the graper, and realized the second I jumped on it how different it was from my own ride.
I didn't know how to put it, but it felt...hard, and kinda cramped. I remembered right away that Cross hadn't modded this thing at all.
But this wasn't the time to grumble about his basic-ass graper!
I snaked my way through the tight roads of Nakano.
I wasn't used to this graper at all, so getting there felt like it was taking way longer than it should have.
Wind suddenly shared some info with me.
I closed it so I could focus on driving.
Riding this hunk of junk was taking all my concentration, so I decided to look at the info once I stopped.
Right! I should change the traffic lights.
To save a little more time, I used my BMI to hack the light in front, changing it from red to green.
A large truck entered the intersection I'd just messed with.
The change in traffic signals was so sudden that not even its AI's automated brakes were fast enough.
I hit the brakes as fast as I could...

scenes.label: *flag_off
texts: Riding my graper, I snaked my way through the tight roads of Nakano.
The business card listed an address south of Nakano Station, in District 2. With a little light hacking, I'd be there in no time.
Wind shared some info with me.
It said some hacker had found the next hint after the JA1037E one.
Wait, it's from six minutes ago!
Other people missed it too. It's not your fault, Windy.
Yeah, but you know, I'm supposed to be, like, the quest guy, so this is kinda pathetic.

scenes.label: *load
texts: How reliable is this hint, anyway? Maybe the others ignored it for a reason.
There's no way to verify it right now. That's why I figured we should all work together and try to make sense of it.
I had to choose between switching my attention to the new hint or concentrating on opening the channel.
The best way would be to Load, then decode the hint right after it was posted. With such a tight time limit, we needed those six minutes.
But we weren't sure the hint was legit, so maybe ignoring would be better?

scenes.label: *select1
texts: All right. I'll go back and wait for the post.

scenes.label: *notload_S3
texts: ...Forget Loading. It was better to focus on my channel plan. I could reconsider Loading if I came to a dead end.
Wind, learn as much as you can. I'll be waiting on some good news from you.
Okaaay! Let's do what we caaan!
It was a pretty huge building. It was sure bigger than I expected a solo detective's office to be, anyway.
It was three stories high, and close to the station too. Looked pretty spacious, like he had a whole floor to himself.
On the second floor! Use the stairs and come up up uppity up!
Wait, this whole building was his?
Momo ran up the stairs beside the door, and I hurried after her.
We heard some sounds, but Nonno was nowhere in sight. She must've been busy working.
Look for this! It should be in storage at the end over there.
Do you know where you last put—
If I did, I'd be looking for it myself!
Good point, but this was tough without any help whatsoever.
Perhaps there's a camera feature or something like that we could use?
I used mine to scan the photo of the repeater, then shared it with Momo.
An AI can help identify what we're looking for. Try to look over every inch of the place.
We started our search at different shelves.

scenes.label: *nonno_voice
texts: Hey, Polly, you know 302's flight path, right?
If Beary-Airy flies as fast as the plane, it'll run out of fuel right away. You gotta shoot it from the right place for this to work.
Huh?! Does that mean that the channel's gonna get cut off fast too?
No-no worries there. I'll equip the drone with a sticky ball firing system so we can stick the repeater to the plane.
So the channel will stay live as long as the repeater's there? You really are a virtuoso.
I'd barely shared any details with her, but she'd already thought the whole thing through.
We had to figure out the flight path.
Wind! You seeing any flight path predictions on 4chan?
Umm, lemme look for posts about the path...
We've got posts about its current location, but no one knows where it's going.
So it's not that easy, huh?
It sucked, but that was pretty much what I'd expected.
